enkin</i>, <i>Jankin</i>; see   Jenkin  ), with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>.","History: Joseph Jenks (1602–83), the descendant of an old Welsh family, was born in England and traveled to Saugus, near Lynn, MA, in 1642 to assist in the development of America's first iron works. His son, Joseph Jenckes (sic), followed in 1650, founded Pawtucket, RI, and raised four sons who held places of respect and distinction in RI, including one who served as governor for five years."]},{"name":"Jenkinson","meanings":["English (Yorkshire and Lancashire): from the Middle English personal names <i>Jankin</i>, <i>Jenkin</i>, or <i>Jonkin</i> (see   Jenkin  ) + <i>son</i>."]}]},{"name":"Gruffudd","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Old Welsh <i>Grip(p)iud</i>, from an unexplained first element + a second element meaning ‘lord, prince’.  Gruffydd ap Llewelyn  (  d. 1063 ) was one of the most able rulers of Wales in the Middle Ages, scoring notable victories over the English until he was eventually defeated by  King Harold  in  1063 ."],"variants":[{"name":"Griffudd","meanings":["From Old Welsh <i>Grip(p)iud</i>, from an unexplained first element + a second element meaning ‘lord, prince’.  Gruffydd ap Llewelyn  (  d. 1063 ) was one of the most able rulers of Wales in the Middle Ages, scoring notable victories over the English until he was eventually defeated by  King Harold  in  1063 ."]},{"name":"Gruffud","meanings":["From Old Welsh <i>Grip(p)iud</i>, from an unexplained first element + a second element meaning ‘lord, prince’.  Gruffydd ap Llewelyn  (  d. 1063 ) was one of the most able rulers of Wales in the Middle Ages, scoring notable victories over the English until he was eventually defeated by  King Harold  in  1063 ."]},{"name":"Griffith","meanings":["Anglicized form of   Gruffudd ."]}]},{"name":"ap","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Loving’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gruffudd ap Jenkin was born about 1323, in Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom, his father, Jenkin Dafydd, was 27 and his mother, Mrs. Jenkin Dafydd, was 23. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs Gruffudd ap Jenkin."},"et":{"ABT    1323–":"umbes 1323–Surnud","1323–Male":"1323–Surnud","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1325–Female":"1325–Surnud","1355–Female":"1355–Surnud","1298–Male":"1298–Surnud","1302–Female":"1302–Surnud","ABT    1323":"umbes 1323","1325":"1325","1302":"1302","1323":"1323","1355":"1355","1298":"1298","1330":"1330","Nanhoron Issa, Lleyn, Caernarvonshire, Wales":"Lleyn, Caernarfonshire, Wales, United Kingdom","of,Aberafan,Glamorganshire,Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Wales":"Wales"},"fi":{"ABT    1323–":"noin 1323–Kuollut","1323–Male":"1323–Kuollut","1330–Male":"1330–Kuollut","1325–Female":"1325–Kuollut","1355–Female":"1355–Kuollut","1298–Male":"1298–Kuollut","1302–Female":"1302–Kuollut","ABT    1323":"noin 1323","1325":"1325","1302":"1302","1323":"1323","1355":"1355","1298":"1298","1330":"1330","Nanhoron Issa, Lleyn, Caernarvonshire, Wales":"Lleyn, Caernarfonshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of,Aberafan,Glamorganshire,Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Wales":"Wales"},"fr":{"ABT    1323–":"environ 1323–Décédé","1323–Male":"1323–Décédé","1330–Male":"1330–Décédé","1325–Female":"1325–Décédée","1355–Female":"1355–Décédée","1298–Male":"1298–Décédé","1302–Female":"1302–Décédée","ABT    1323":"environ 1323","1325":"1325","1302":"1302","1323":"1323","1355":"1355","1298":"1298","1330":"1330","Nanhoron Issa, Lleyn, Caernarvonshire, Wales":"Lleyn, Caernarfonshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","of,Aberafan,Glamorganshire,Wales":"Glamorgan, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","Wales":"Galles","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Gruffudd ap Jenkin est né environ 1323, à Glamorgan, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni, son père, Jenkin Dafydd, avait 27 ans et sa mère, 